compete multiple contractor solutions through a three phased competitive selection process. Phase 1 concluded with the evaluation of the three contractor solutions
through a demonstration event and transitioned to Phase 2 with two vendors selected to continue into performance test and evaluation. The ATV-S program has entered
Phase 2, Prototype Testing and Operational Demonstration with two awarded contractors. The best value solution from Phase 2 will transition to Phase 3 to build
additional prototypes for First Unit Issued (FUI) to support the Army Transportation Company level evaluation required to gain operational feedback to support an
approved follow-on Acquisition Pathway.

 The Leader Follower (Autonomous Transport Vehicle-System (ATV-S) program) will seek a follow-on production acquisition pathway approval to award a production
 contract to the MTA - Rapid Prototyping Phase 3 selected contractor. This follow-on production acquisition will include a production contract award, software support
 and development, training, fielding. The production contract will include refurbishment of the MTA - Rapid Prototyping FUI prototypes to fieldable assets for First Unit
 Equipped (FUE), new production quantities, contractor logistics support until Army organic support is achieved, software support and software development.

