This Project matures and demonstrates advanced sensor technologies that characterize hazards posed to warfighters by non-weaponized biological hazards in
subterranean environments. Demonstrations of previously developed sensor packages and adaptive commercial off the shelf sensor technologies on existing unmanned
ground vehicles (UGV) platforms to gather end-user feedback. The capabilities resulting from this project provide Soldiers the capability to understand biological hazards
present in subterranean environments and take necessary steps to mitigate or avoid these threats.

