D. Acquisition Strategy
The Alternative Navigation Ground Control Segment (ALTNAV GCS) utilizes a mix of Federal Acquisition Regulation contracts. The program received Middle Tier of
Acquisition Rapid Fielding (MTA-RF) approval in May 2024. The MTA-RF program will span FY24-FY27. This will provide incremental capability to use and inform future
Alternative PNT capabilities along with Mounted and Dismounted Assured Positioning, Navigation, and Timing requirements.

 Requirement documents include:
 - ALTNAV Abbreviated Capabilities Development Document (A-CDD), Army Requirements Oversight Council (AROC) Approved, 29 August 2022.
 - DAPS Capabilities Development Document (CDD), Joint Requirements Oversight Council (JROC) Approved, 28 January 2022.
 - MAPS Capabilities Development Document (CDD), Army Requirements Oversight Council (AROC) Approved, 12 September 2020.
 - Alternative Navigation (ALTNAV) DR, 10 August 2019.




