A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The ELMS system provides accountability and management functionality of General Equipment, Real Property and Internal Use Software, to the Department. The
budgeted projects will provide enhancements to the existing capability, ensure efficient operation, and provide solutions for process gaps as they are discovered. The
greater enhancements to ELMS allow the DoW to sunset legacy systems as ELMS assimilates the legacy functionality into the overall operations.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                      FY 2025            FY 2026     FY 2027
Title: Technical Refresh                                                                                                                     2.894              3.020       2.829
Description: FY25 Accomplishments:
- Developed a process to load the Joint Strike Fighter (JSF) Contract Data Requirement List (CDRL)s data to produce values for
financial statement.
- Completed the data load process for 43 out of 100 Air Force programs to enable financial reporting of Government Furnished
Property.

FY 2026 Plans:
The program plans to Merge Marine Corps Platform Integration Center (MCPIC) with ELMS, Replace Global Combat Support
System - Marine Corps (GCSS-MC), Replace Relational Supply for the Navy, and Implement Air Force Unit Level Supply.
FY 2027 Plans:
Currently, ELMS is the only Accountable Property System of Record (APSR) within DoW that has achieved full compliance and
demonstrable auditability and will enable the DoW to meet the Congressionally mandated 2028 deadline. The program plans
to implement the Marine Corps Fleet into DPAS, Joint Strike Fighter (JSF) and other programs within the Services and DOW
Agencies.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Decrease in FY27 due to reprioritization of requirements.
